inn1.comm: full outside off, Cook comes forward and defends to cover
touch shorter this time, played off the back foot this time to the off side
goes fuller, brings Cook into a drive which squirts off a thick outside edge but safely down to third man
full at off stump, pushed back to the bowler
gets across his stumps and defends towards midwicket
on middle and leg, worked into the on side towards midwicket...steady opening over from Faulkner
good start, full at off stump, 139kph, defended square to point
hint of swing, but it started too straight and it's neatly flicked through midwicket...deep square gets around
left alone outside off, 140kph
on a length outside off, Cook hangs back and defends to cover
shorter delivery, on leg stump, pitch appears a touch slow and Cook has plenty of time to ride this into the leg side
nice delivery, back of a length outside off and it comes into Bell, in the air then off the seam, as he shoulders arms
gets forward outside off stump, defended to cover
superb stroke by Cook, manufactures an on-drive as he fetches this from outside off and drills it firmly straight of mid-on a lot of bottom hand
pulls the length back a little and it's play to cover with another positive stride
excellent delivery, beats Cook with a shorter delivery outside off and the batsman was walking into his shot
cuts to backward point who doesn't stop it cleanly so allows a single
now Bell gets one through the infield, full on middle and off and whipped strongly wide of mid-on over what is a pretty quick outfield
more intent from Cook, some width offered and drives up and over cover...intentionally in the air
back-to-back boundaries, driven strongly square of the wicket this time as Pattinson again offers up a fraction of width
a little tighter to off stump, Cook leaves this one alone
short of a length, Cook goes back and defends towards the bowler
worked nicely off the pads, short of a length again and placed through midwicket
full outside off, adjusts well to the right hander, defended to point
short of a length on off stump, defended square of the wicket
defended from the back foot towards cover
dropped in short and Cook responds with a thumping pull shot, in front of square and it clears the deep square-leg boundary...positive signs from the England captain
back of a length, 140kph, on off stump and this time it's defence from Cook
fuller on middle and off, punched firmly towards mid-on
short on leg stump, another nice piece of timing as he flicks it behind square off his pads but Pattinson gets around and slides to cut off the boundary
aggression now from Bell, hammers a length ball towards cover on the up but straight to the fielder
another boundary, not quite so convincing this time as Bell advances down the pitch then flicks it just out of reach of Coulter-Nile at short fine leg
big top edge! Runs flowing. Banged in short, Bell went for the pull and it flies straight back over the keep and slips
back of a full length outside off, defended firmly to cover
back of a length, cramping Bell for room a little so he just defends
short of a length, Bell tries to force it through the off side off the back foot but mistimes it back to the bowler
pushed across outside off, left alone
fuller at off stump, Cook onto the front foot and drives to mid-off
flicks this from a full length at middle stump towards mid-on
gets a cut shot away again but it goes straight to third man
extra effort in that delivery, 142kph, and it beats Bell over the top edge as he tries to upper cut it over the slips
and this goes through the vacant slip cordon, although was fairly controlled by Bell as he came down the pitch then opened the face towards third man
starts round the wicket to Cook who defends
beautifully played by Cook, he chips down the pitch then flicks this in the air over midwicket and it's placed wide of the sweeper
now he pulls a short ball through the same area, Cook quick to spot the error in length and latched on

and what a comeback! Or is it? Given lbw as it beats Cook on the back foot. He's called for a review. Has it pitched outside leg? There's no edge for sure. It's pitched on but missing on height. Cook survives.
fuller on off stump, forward and defends
now he's beaten by one that skids across outside off stump, he was trying to guide it through short third man
dropped at short point by Finch. It was hammered off the back foot by Bell, it was a good height but was certainly going at a rate of knots
angled down to third man to bring up England's fifty
defended to cover

gone this time! Just went it appeared things had turned for Cook he drives off the back foot to a short of a length delivery and Maxwell dives to his right at cover to hold a good catch. He was right to attack that delivery, just didn't get over he top of the shot.
short ball straight over off stump, he sways out of the line
full on off stump, gets forward and defends to cover
on off stump, defended towards mid-off
tries to work this into space on the off side but picks out cover
short of a length, driven firmly off the back foot to point
gets cramped for room, it was a slightly slower delivery and appeared to grip in the pitch, Bell was early on his shot and it takes an inside edge to the leg side
this time he gets it over the off stump, advances down on the line of leg stump and slices it over point although the timing was quite there
full outside off, left alone
on leg stump, flicked just wide of short fine leg and Stokes hustles through for a sharp single
round the wicket, outside off, defended to point
tucked off middle stump to midwicket
dragged down a little short, Stokes goes onto the back foot and pulls through midwicket
uses his feet but ends up yorking himself and just bunts the ball towards mid-on
pushed firmly back to the bowler
round the wicket, full at the stumps, worked down the ground to long-on
a touch short and pull into midwicket, again not quite timed
comes forward, opens the face and placed through point
Bell does a Maxwell to Maxwell...brings out the reverse sweep, there's a fair bit of top edge involved but it loops well over short third man
fuller at middle, driven down to long-on
flicked into midwicket
worked from off stump to midwicket
stretches forward and places it down to long-on
delicate this time from Bell, brings out the reverse paddle but picks out short third man
angled in towards middle and leg, flicked to midwicket
driven into the off side
placed nicely off the back foot through the off side, he wanted two quite early on but Stokes sent him back
round the wicket, tickled to short fine leg
uses his feet this time and pushed down to long-on
gets an inside edge into his pads as he plays forward
a fraction shorter and played off the back foot down the ground
plays the slog sweep, the shot he got out to in Melbourne, has to reach for it a fair bit as it's on off stump but connects well to deep square
drifts into Stokes, strangled appeal for lbw but wasn't particularly close

direct hit! Warner has pulled off a stunning run out. England continue to create their own problems. It was played square through the off side, Bell didn't really hesitate on coming for the second but Warner just swooped too quickly. He had one stump to aim at from side on and was deadly accurate from about half way to the boundary. Bell well short. Brilliant fielding
round the wicket, works his first ball from outside off to short fine leg
defended to the off side
off the mark with a scampered single to mid-on who is now inside the circle
flicked along the ground to midwicket
played into the off side
drifts onto leg stump, tucked out to deep square
shorter on leg stump, worked off the pads through the leg side
flicked out to deep square-leg
fuller at off stump, defended into the off side
traps this off a thick inside edge to the leg side
nearly gets this under Stokes' bat, fired in very full, he tried to open up the off side and just managed to get a toe end on it
worked to square leg
touch shorter, pushed off the back foot back to the bowler
gets forward this time and worked straight to midwicket
nearly another run out! Tucked to square leg and he was well down the pitch but managed to dive back
driven into the off side, Doherty fields himself
can't get it past Doherty on the on side and that's a maiden
pushed to the off side
cut towards short third man
turn for Maxwell, beats the outside edge as Stokes lunges forward...becoming harder for these two batsmen
driven straight down to long-on
pushed to short cover
hint of width, he cuts firmly but can't beat point...England coming to a standstill against these two spinners
full on leg stump, goes for a sweep but it just takes the pad
touch shorter, goes onto the back foot but can't beat midwicket
gets the sweep away this time, was outside leg stump, runs to deep square leg
reverse sweep this time, doesn't go further than short third man
flicked firmly off middle stump, again finds the man at midwicket
fuller and beats midwicket on this occasion as he works it away with a strong bottom
plenty of flight from Maxwell and it's driven through cover
driven back to the bowler on the bounce
a little flatter and quicker, Stokes goes back to cut hard and just beats Clarke at point
driven through cover for another single
delicate from Stokes, soft hands as he dabs this past the keeper and it's cut off in the circle
driven down the ground to long-on
punched away to midwicket but good fielding by Maxwell in the circle, cuts off the single
goes the cut but this beats the bat
tossed up from around the wicket and it's fullish, the drive can't beat mid on
driven uppishly and short of mid-off, Ballance just can't find the gaps here
and now Ballance does find a way to score, he's got to the pitch of this and driven it over mid-off, a good proper shot that bounces away to the boundary
wristy flick from Ballance finds square leg
driven down the ground for the easy single to long on
nudged away through the covers and the man in the deep keeps it to one
Stokes advances and lofts this inside out over and that's bounced away to Warner in the deep

Maxwell has got through the defences of Stokes with one that goes on with the arm, that looked plumb but Stokes is asking for a review of the lbw! And again the bounce has tricked umpire Martinesz - and this commentator - that was sailing a fraction over the top of the stumps. But Stokes got a big stride down the pitch, and that has saved him.
defended back towards the bowler
driven away down the ground to long-on for the easy single again
Stokes goes the big sweep to a ball down leg but he misses - and the ball hits him on the pad
again Doherty goes for a leg-side line and Stokes advances, can't get bat on ball and it flies off his pad
Stokes goes back into his crease to defend

Clarke has taken a stunner at square leg! Holy moly batsman, that is a remarkable catch! Stokes has gone for the sweep and smoked it out of the middle of the bat, Clarke at square leg has had to react instantly and does so, dives to his right and thrusts the right hand low to the ground and the ball sticks - that was tougher than most catches he'd get in the cordon. Super take.
defended back down the pitch
angled across Morgan from around the wicket, and it's driven down to mid-off
worked away to the leg side by Ballance
Ballance drops this at his feet and thinks about stealing a single but Morgan sends him back
Pattinson just gets the line a touch wrong here, slipping it fractionally down leg side for a wide
banged in at the hips and worked away to leg for a single
angled across Morgan, who leaves it alone
solid in defence now
once more Morgan is watchfully leaving outside off
clipped away through the leg side for another single
Morgan gets off the mark with a nudge down the ground to long-on
clipped through midwicket to the man in the deep
again worked away to midwicket, can't beat the fielder in the circle now
cut away behind point for another single
once again the man at short midwicket prevents a run
short of a length from Pattinson and Morgan nudges a single to leg
well played by Ballance, gets the width he's been denied for a while and crunches a cut hard over the top of point for a pretty safe boundary
down leg now from Pattinson, just getting his line wrong here
fuller and angled across Ballance, who drives uppishly off a thickish edge through cover point
Morgan cuts forward of point for another single
lovely cover-drive here from Ballance as he comes forward and times it nicely through the gap in the infield but there is a sweeper who cuts off the boundary
Pattinson goes the slower ball now - and oversteps - and Ballance guides it off the face to third man
Morgan gets the free hit and Pattinson's short ball on leg is pulled away for a boundary to fine leg
nudged away for a single
leans forward to punch it back to Doherty
Morgan backs off a touch now and punches wide of mid-off
drifting in from around the wicket and it's pushed away to long on
on middle and leg again and worked through midwicket
again worked straight to the man in the circle at midwicket
slowish outside off and Morgan waits on a late cut towards third man
104kph from Christian - almost a Chris Harris-style effort this - and it's pushed away to off
he's taking all the pace off the ball here - 109kph - and it's pushed through leg
angled in from around the wicket and it's driven to mid-on
slow again, and again the batsman can't quite force the pace to get it through the field
wide of off and steered away to third man off the face of the bat
driven down towards mid-on
pushed away through the gap at cover for a single

Coulter-Nile makes the breakthrough, and it's a rather poor piece of placement from Ballance. He's got some width and went the cut shot but sliced it upwards and Christian was out at deep point and ran in to take a reasonably comfortable catch
Morgan drops it at the feet but doesn't want a single
left alone outside off
driven towards cover and can't find the gap
Christian is over the wicket now to Bopara and continues to take the pace off the ball, it's defended
swinging in towards off stump and Bopara defends
107kph and Bopara nudges it to leg, he's trying to get used to the pace here
Christian goes for the leg-stump yorker now and overpitches just a touch, Bopara clips behind square leg and runs hard for two
driven away through cover - and I mean through - as a diving Clarke seemed to have that covered and then got a horrid bounce that sees the ball bounce over him - and mid-off backs up
worked away for another single
good running from Bopara as he calls a quick single with his nudge just forward of point
another quick single as Morgan steers it down into the turf and Haddin gets around to collect it
accurate from Coulter-Nile on off stump, Bopara defends
left alone outside off
Bopara opens the face and steers this past the sole slip away to third man
Morgan leans out to push this to mid-off and makes a loud shout of "nooooo"
goes well wide of off now and Bopara can't beat point
116kph now and Bopara steers a single through the vacant cordon
Morgan defends solidly to the off side, seems cautious about going after Christian at this slow pace
Morgan goes back into his crease and bunts to leg, can't justify a single
bad ball - that's what Christian can't afford to do - he drops it short and Morgan has no trouble at all pulling this in the air behind square leg for a boundary
wide of off now and Morgan punches a single to deep point
around the wicket and accurate from Maxwell - Morgan goes back and cuts
still around the wicket to Bopara, who advances and just nudges to leg
pushed away to the leg side again and can't find the gap
down leg side and tickled off the pad for a single - ah, but the umpire has called a dead ball, deciding Bopara hadn't played a shot
flicked through square leg for one run
almost round-arm from Maxwell now as he skids this flat one on and Morgan defends
Bopara waits on this ball from Christian and forces a quick single to mid-off, where Pattinson fumbles
cuts hard into the ground and Morgan picks up one more, the runs trickling slowly here
a touch short from Christian outside off and Bopara's pull through midwicket is collected in the deep

again Morgan latches on to a short ball from Christian, he's pulled it hard and just forward of deep midwicket, who for a moment seemed he may have a catching chance, but this bounces away for a boundary
fuller now and driven back to Christian
steered away towards backward point
Maxwell is around the wicket to Bopara, who tickles one to short fine leg
driven away to extra cover and can't pierce the gap
Morgan leans out of his crease to defend
Morgan rocks back to late cut but there's a deep backward point who cuts this off
skids across the right-hander and beats the bat - it was an attempted glance to third man
Bopara again can't get bat on ball, tries to force a cut to a skiddy ball
defended back towards Faulkner
Morgan has decided with the field up it's time to go, and go he does! Advances to Faulkner and lifts this over extra cover with such timing that it's sailed into the stands for six!
now he picks up a single down to long-on
Bopara nudges this away to leg
now he gets a single through square leg to give Morgan another chance in this over
Morgan just drops this into the off side and takes off for a well-judged single
Morgan drives through point and one of the men in the deep is out there to cut the ball off
worked away comfortably through square leg for another one
Morgan gets forward to cover drive again but only a single
good accurate bouncer mixes things up - haven't seen too many of them in this match - and Bopara just sways out of the way
again this is on the rise as it gets through to Haddin, some good extra bounce sails past Bopara at chest height
tickled away to fine leg for a single
on leg stump, worked into the square-leg area
pushed square into the off side with an open face
fuller at off stump, Bopara on-drives and beats Faulkner who dives in his follow through
gives himself room to leg, Faulkner drags down a slower ball and Morgan only connects with fresh air
fuller on middle and leg, pushed firmly down to long-on
dropped behind square on the off side with soft hands...careful stuff from England
worked off his pads behind square on the leg side and it's placed well enough for a second
short of a length outside off, on his toes and drives square but can't quite split point and cover as Christian gets a hand on it with a dive
that's huge! Takes a step down the pitch then lofts a length ball straight down the ground. It went miles into the air (if they'd been a roof etc) but it also had the length to reach the crowd
back of a length this time, defended to the off side...screams 'no' first of all then realises he can trot a single
tries to work this into midwicket from outside off stump
this one pings out of the middle, he piled into that pull stroke as Coulter-Nile dropped short but couldn't beat Finch on the deep square-leg boundary
short this time from Faulkner, Bopara pulls again but this one isn't time as well as it was tighter to his body
low full toss, he can't beat midwicket
back of a length, another dot ball as it's played to the on side
angled into the pads, flicked away behind square and Morgan makes it into a comfortable second
dropped into the off side, the fielders inside the ring are quite deep
excellent catch! Bopara trying to run it down to third man, opened the face outside off stump and Haddin dives to his right
he gets reverse swept first ball, connects really cleanly and gets it well wide of short third man to take him to another half-century from 54 balls. He is in great form.
plays orthodox this time, driven down to long-off
full from round the wicket, flicked through midwicket
opens his stance and drives square through the off side to deep point
worked down the ground, long-off this time
pushed out to cover
short of a length outside off, driven firmly but straight to cover
there's a slower one, 106kph, Buttler waits for it and works out to deep square

what a catch! Christian in his follow through. Or is it? Morgan isn't taking the fielder's word for it. Christian was convinced, but the batsman has stood his ground. A few ugly scenes in the middle. Clarke isn't happy with Morgan. The umpires are stepping in. Well, we need another replay here. Tough to tell at first glance. Has it got his fingers under it? Yes, he has.  He's given. Morgan has to walk off and gets booed as he does. Back to the ball itself, another cutter from Christian which held in the pitch, Morgan tried to work it away and got a looping edge that looped into the off side. Christian sprinted from his follow through, dived forward, and grasped it just above the turf.
cuts and misses first ball
worked off the stumps to midwicket
full outside off, very nicely driven through the off side and beats deep cover
short of a length, nips into Buttler and it takes an outside edge to cover
short of a length, angled in the air down to third man
another one guided to third man
sharp delivery, 145kph, short of a length and angled into Buttler who fends it behind square
back of a length, defended to the off side
width this time, a slower ball at 121kph, and driven out to cover
outside leg stump but it only costs a single as Bresnan flicks straight to long leg

massive wicket! That could kill off any late charge. Lack of pace doing for Buttler. It was outside off stump, around 105kph, Buttler tries to force through the off side and gets a big inside edge into the stumps

nearly another return catch. Broad drives at a cutter and it falls just short of Christian diving to his right...and then he was nearly run out as he wander down the pitch and cover hurled the ball back
pushed back to the bowler
off the mark with a flick through midwicket
tucked through midwicket...singles won't hurt Australia
angled into the body, takes the thigh pad to the leg side
that's a bit of a shocker from Broad. Short of a length, Broad goes for the pull and it goes straight up the air off a top edge which Haddin settles underneath
full and driven back to the bowler
that's the 200 up with a strong pull by Bresnan, splits deep square and long leg
runs it down to third man
worked into midwicket, gets a scamper on to make his ground and keep the strike
full at off stump, 118kph, defended to cover
taken off the stumps through midwicket
full at middle, clipped in the air through the leg side...England just have to bat out the overs now
beats him outside off with a full delivery that grips a touch on the surface...Haddin whips off the bails. Jordan's foot was up for a fraction of a second, but got back
shorter and pulled down to long leg
tight to off stump, he cuts and can't split backward point and short third man
clubbed into midwicket but can't beat the man inside the ring
finds the gap this time, full and angling into the pads again, he swings hard and gets it wide of the diving midwicket
goes to the on side again, it was fuller and not as well timed so midwicket cuts it off
back of a length, Jordan can't do anything else than jab to the off side
full and straight, gets this one into space on the leg side
he hooks, well controlled as he managed to roll his wrists but long leg keeps them to a single
full at off stump, driven firmly into the pitch and Christian fields it one-handed to his right
driven down to long-on
full and straight, flicked to short fine-leg
keeping it full, on leg stump this time, no width for Bresnan who drives to long-on
outside off, he drives and it comes off a thick outside to short third man
low full toss but it doesn't go further than deep midwicket. A good over from Christian
full at middle, jabbed into the leg side
goes for the surprise bouncer and it beats Jordan's pull
that's a clean blow! Short again, but not quite so short, and this time Jordan connects out of the middle and pulls in front of square

this time he picks out the fielder...another good catch. Jordan trying to go over the leg side again, gets height but not the distance - needed to fetch it from outside off - and Finch steadied himself at deep square-leg
placed backward of point wide of third man so Bresnan can keep the strike
yorker outside off, he can't get it further than back to the bowler
round the wicket, full on middle, worked down to long-on
that's into the second tier over deep midwicket! Christian just got the length slightly, on a length, allowing him to get underneath and launch it clear into the stands
and again! Late boost for England. This time it was shorter and he pulled it, not quite so well time as the previous one but enough brute force to just clear Maxwell at deep midwicket
gets the yorker in, driven down the ground
opens the face to backward point to give Bresnan the last ball
inches from another boundary...Bresnan lapped a low full toss from outside off, but Coulter-Nile pulled off a terrific dive at short fine leg so it's just a single

inn2.comm: can't get bat on the first one, this lobs off the body in front of Finch after he tried to turn it to leg

oh dear, what is going on out there? Warner has nearly been run out without facing a ball. Finch has punched it to cover and called a single, Warner basically gave up on the run about three-quarters down the pitch but the throw missed
full and straight, Warner can't beat mid-on
swings down leg side and that is called a wide
some width now and Warner slashes outside off but it beats the bat
some inswing now from Jordan, strikes Warner on the leg as he can't get it away
on the back foot Warner punches to extra cover and takes off for a well judged single
quick single immediately as Warner pushes to mid off and takes off
defended back down the pitch to the bowler
strays on to the pads now and Finch clips this behind square leg for the first boundary of the innings
takes off for a quick leg bye on to the leg side
super placement from Warner as he gets some width and rocks on to the back foot to crunch this through extra cover, piercing the field and sending it along the ground to the boundary
defended away to the off side now
on the pads and Finch has no trouble clipping this away behind square for a couple
on the back foot Finch flicks it again through the leg side as Jordan gets a touch too straight
this time Finch plays straighter and can't find the gap
wide of off at 144kph and Finch punches behind point for a single
inswing to Warner's leg-stump line and it's defended
too much down leg from Jordan, who just can't quite find his line, and Warner easily works it through square leg
another very quick single as Warner pushes to off and runs immediately, good judgment
down leg side and Finch can't get anything on it, so that's a wide
better line now just outside off and Finch defends
on the pads again and those are easy runs - clipped through square leg
Warner nudges this off the hips to leg for another comfortable single
better from Broad, a touch of away swing and outside off, that's where you may just get Finch early in his innings - he pushes it to point
and back to the pads - Finch clips it through square again
better line outside off from Jordan and Finch pushes it away through point
fullish and on off stump, Warner drives down towards mid-off
Jordan at 146kph here, tempts Warner outside off but it's not as short as Warner thought - his cut misses
shorter now and on the leg stump, Warner pulls it around the corner down to fine leg
Finch is solid in defence now on off stump
thumpingly strong straight drive from Aaron Finch now, he's got a fullish straight ball and punched it back from whence it came - so straight it's very nearly hit the non-striker's stumps.
Broad at 137kph now and tempting Warner into the drive, which finds mid-off
cuts it down into the ground and can't beat point
crunches a cut away that isn't quite timed
muscular pull now from Warner, really well timed through midwicket as Broad just gives him a short ball that is of no real threat - chest height.
gets back into his crease to defend now
clipped off the pads now as the line is wrong again
England just can't get their bowling right - this is yet another one skewed down leg for a wide

there's an lbw shout here and Jordan is pretty interested but the umpire isn't - Finch drove hard at a straight ball. England decide against a review and it's a good call - there was an inside edge there.
straight ball, straight punch that is collected by mid-on
Warner waits on this one and steers it to point
clipped off the pads and away to fine leg
Finch gets on the back foot now and crunches it through point, fine timing and placement

Jordan has struck! The runs were flowing but Finch couldn't stop himself driving hard in the air and there is a man at cover who has no trouble holding this catch. He'll be disappointed with himself there - just couldn't keep that along the ground
on the back foot now, Warner defends
what a shot! Warner has picked a length ball and just hit right through it, driving hard and down the ground over long-off, with enough timing to clear the boundary
outside off and through to the keeper
Warner falls over now as he nudges this to leg and gets in a bit of a tangle
probes outside off and Warner defends with a straight bat

oh, Warner has nearly joined Finch back in the rooms! He's gone for the pull from a shortish ball but didn't get hold of it, the top edge flies out and lobs just over the head of the midwicket - that wasn't far away at all
cuts hard and it's collected at point
Warner waits on this and cuts away towards third man
punched away off the pads to midwicket
cuts hard and finds the man in the infield
Warner gets back into his crease and defends from outside off
fuller and straighter and Warner clips it through mid-on, who fumbles - Tim Bresnan it was - and lets a one become a two
Marsh finally gets to face a ball after two overs at the non-striker's end - he gets off the mark with a nudge to leg
short ball from Bresnan and Warner has nailed this pull, he was very quickly on to that and pulled it up into the air, wide of the man at deep midwicket and it's one bounce over the boundary
shortish outside off now and Warner tries to dab at that, misses the ball though
really good placement once again - Warner has cut this hard off the back foot and found the gap between point and cover
fuller and outside off, Warner pushes to point
another boundary now as Warner gets on on the hips and glances it wide of fine leg, who is in the circle, which in turn means that is always going to run away for four
Marsh nudges a quick single to the off side
Tredwell sneaks in with his quick action and Warner punches a single down to mid-off
Marsh leans out to defend
tossed up a fraction more, and wide of off, Marsh drives through cover
on the stumps and a touch slower, no real spin though and Warner defends
Warner punches a single out to deep cover
lovely delivery from Bresnan as this one pitches on leg and nips away off the seam - moves too far, in fact, as that has beaten Warner's outside edge by quite a way
steered away through point
on the back foot and Marsh defends
Marsh waits on this one and cuts very late, just a single though to third man
worked off the pads through square leg and that's very good running as they turn this into two
tickled away off the leg behind square
tossed up from around the wicket, it's defended from middle stump
turned away through square for a single
tossed up outside off at 84kph and it's defended
this one does for Marsh and nearly tickles his edge! It has turned just a fraction, and just enough to trick Marsh, who thought it was the straight one
defended away to the off side
Marsh again defends carefully
Warner drives hard down the ground but this is cut off by mid-off - that ball was flying!
slower ball at 117kph and Warner picks it well enough to just nudge to the off side and hare off for a quick single
good line on middle and off, Marsh square up a little and pushes it to point
a little too short from Bresnan and Marsh swivels a pull through square leg and through the gap
full and wide of off, Marsh drives hard and thinks it's through but Tredwell at mid-off has done super well to dive and cut that off one-handed - that was a boundary otherwise
play and miss outside off
a tiny bit of turn, but not much - it's pushed away to the off side
Warner uses the feet now and drives but straight to cover
Warner drives down the ground for the easy single available to long-off
Marsh tries to whip this through leg but can't beat mid-on
good use of the feet from Marsh and he clips this straight enough on the leg side that it beats mid-on - fine placement as that runs away to the boundary
worked away through leg for a single now
fullish on the stumps and driven away through cover
some width for Marsh, who late cuts this along the ground to third man
tries for the yorker length ball on leg but it's clipped away for a single
skiddy on off stump and Marsh pushes to off
Bopara pitches on leg and Marsh closes the face to work it away into the on side but the bowler does some sharp fielding off his own bowling

is this a catch? No! Oh boy, that was close. Angled across Marsh, who drove hard outside off and it flew low towards backward point, where Morgan dived forward and took the ball pretty cleanly, but it must have been on the half-volley as he wasn't interested in asking the question about a catch. That has only just bounced short.
defended from the off-stump line, no real turn there
there's the half-century for Warner, from his 56th delivery, and he does it with an easy enough single, just a punch through cover point off a ball that was a touch too short
uses the feet now and clips this through square leg, good sharp running turns this into a two
leans forward to defend
this one just goes on with the arm into the left-hander, he pushes it to leg
defended away to the off side now
back of a length on off stump, dropped into the off side and another scampered single...he's so hard to stop
full and wide, driven very hard through square cover to the sweeper
straighter, driven to mid-off
slips down the leg side so that's an extra run and delivery
driven through point
an appeal for lbw from Bopara, but no else...it pitched outside leg
poor line, worked off leg stump backward of square on the leg side...almost runs away from the fielder
uses his feet then works through midwicket
tossed up a little more, makes it into a low full toss as he comes down the pitch and it's another run through midwicket
down the pitch again, driven through a tightly packed off-side field
nice touch play this time, opens the face and places it between point and cover
all the way...Warner couldn't resist any longer, he goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps over deep midwicket
touch quicker and flatter, no surprise there, and tucked into midwicket
he's on a roll, doesn't allow Broad to settle in, it's a length delivery on the stumps and Warner lofts it over mid-off. Wasn't out of the middle. Didn't matter.
more energy on this delivery, 137kph, and beats Warner as he goes for a cut
defended firmly back to Broad who they hurls the ball back pas the stumps to Buttler
back of a length, tries to turn this to the leg side and it comes off a leading edge to cover
pushed firmly towards mid-off and another of those singles that have characterised this innings as much as the boundaries
round the wicket, on off stump, defended
and he's greeted like Broad was, width outside off, full, and driven through cover with disdain
and it brings his downfall! Aims for a repeat dose but this time drives straight to cover. A little careless, if you are honest, because he had England at his mercy and a hundred on offer.
on off stump, tries to get forward and the ball takes the inside edge through square leg
full at leg stump, takes the pad to the leg side
onto the front foot, pushed square to point
back of a length, tries to drop and run into the off side but cover is quickly in
back of a length outside off, opens the face on the back foot and places it wide of third man
full at off stump, driven sweetly straight and Broad gets a hand on it in his followthrough
keeps it full, driven to cover
shorter delivery, Clarke works it off his pads behind square
round the wicket, outside off, opens the face and runs it wide of slip to third man
low full toss and he drives it between cover and mid-off, but it came from low the bat so didn't quite reach the boundary
that's a cracking shot from Clarke, leans into a full delivery and drills it straight the ground
not quite so full this time, onto the front foot and driven again but this time Stokes can stop it
back of a length at off stump, goes for the pull but wasn't quite short enough and it comes off a bottom/inside edge to fine leg
worked off the stumps into midwicket
outside off, left alone
well, this short ball had him in some trouble, skidded onto Clarke has went to pull and it was an unconvincing shot that whistled down to fine leg
round the wicket, neatly taken from around off stump out to deep square
full and wide, driven through the covers...Bopara chases it down near the rope
chopped down to third man...rotating between the left and right hander
there's the short ball but it's shoved down the leg side
full outside off, driven back down the pitch
dropped in short, but not really with aggression, sits up comfortable and Clarke pulls through midwicket
outside off, Clarke leaves it alone
comes down the pitch straight away then flicks to midwicket
beats him this time as Marsh opens the face to try and guide down to third man...some turn and bounce
played square into the off side
gets the back-cut away this time but finds short third time
punched off the back foot back to Tredwell
it's an edge, but a controlled one as it guides this very fine past Buttler
full outside off, driven on the up to cover
tight on off stump, defended and it runs to point
pushed into midwicket from a full length
short of a length going across Marsh, he chops into the off side
that's a crunching off drive, tempting length from Jordan, but he picked out mid-off
he drives again, this time up and over mid-on...it wasn't a bad delivery, back of a length. A hint of Warner in that.
round the wicket, Clarke uses his feet and places it through straight midwicket...Marsh slips to prevent any chance of a second
nicely bowled, flighted on middle and there's a hint of turn as Marsh plays to cover
driven down to long-off
dragged down short but get gets away with it as Clarke pulls to square leg
down the pitch again, it's so natural for Clarke, and pushed down to long-on
now Marsh uses his feet as well, not quite so light as Clarke but just as effective as he then works down the ground
close! Just wide of cover. Marsh drives on the up and it goes wide of a diving Bell as he leaps to his left. Bottom hand came off the bat. Maybe a slower delivery which stopped in the pitch
flicked away from off stump through square leg
driven firmly back at Jordan, Clarke going very hard at the ball in this innings. Wants the job done.
back of a length, on off stump, defended
tough chance! Driven on the up by Clarke, back at Jordan to his left and he doesn't time its grab probably and the ball is past him. Didn't come back as hard as the Warner catch in Brisbane
lovely stroke, flicked sweetly through square leg just to make Jordan feel even better
driven out to the cover sweeper
back of a length outside off, hint of shape back into Clarke who defends
big full toss, Clarke doesn't time his whip to the leg side but still gets a couple to deep square
through him! Bopara had just been starting to find some movement into Clarke, this time the Australian captain left a big gap as he drove and the ball snaked back to hit off stump.
driven on the up into the off side
he's really getting it to move (he often does) and this one beats Marsh who was prodding at it without much footwork
full at off stump, clipped to the right of mid-on who dives but then parries the ball away from him to allow a second
defended off the back foot towards mid-on, it's Bresnan there and he's on his heels a bit
full on middle and off, whipped very firmly towards mid-on where Broad can't stop it cleanly
defended to point
big shout for lbw, he's a long way across his stumps but height will be the issue and Cook declines a review
full outside off, Haddin hanging back a touch in the crease as he defends to cover
continues to cause some problems, this time Marsh gets a think bottom edge on a cut which bobbles back quite close to the stumps
this one is a touch fuller and he works it down to long-on
back of a length outside off, punched to cover
tries something expansive, it's a full delivery and he gives himself a touch of room then drills to mid-off
defended on the back foot to midwicket
shaping in from outside off, driven to mid-off
starts with a full toss which is dispatched through midwicket with a strong bottom-handed flick
attempted yorker, he's not far off but Marsh is able to squeeze it out to deep square leg
tucked wide of mid-on
short of a length, loops off the thigh pad and it's a sharpish single as Buttler races in to field
early on a drive and it loops into the off side but short of cover
short of a length on the hip, gets inside the line and tucks down to fine leg
round the wicket, defended to backward point
edged! Did it carry to Cook at slip? Was very low, hit him full on the ankle so technically a chance
defended to the leg side
down the pitch, aiming to the leg side but it goes straight back to Tredwell
just a hint of width and he powers away a cut shot backward of point...takes him to his second fifty. Taking his chance at No. 3
short on leg stump, nicely whipped behind square and it nearly reaches the rope well but there's a sprawling save
driven out to deep cover
on off stump, pushed into the off side and midwicket does well to cut off a single
defended to cover
driven to mid-on
beats everyone, nipping back again and scoots past the inside edge then Buttler fails to glove it
straight drive which is so straight it crashes into the non-striker's stumps
driven down to long-on
defended on the back foot
fuller this time, he leans forward and turns it into midwicket
picks out midwicket
full on off stump, defended
touch quicker, runs off an open face wide of slip to short third man
Marsh flicks off the pads and picks up a single
Haddin goes back in his crease to defend
well now, Haddin is not waiting! He wants this over as quickly as possible, he just backs off a touch and slogs this over cow corner, with such timing that it's cleared the boundary for six
the runs are flowing as Haddin backs off again but this time opens the face to quite deliberately slice this over the men at backward point and short third man - nobody back there in the deep
tries for the big leg-side swipe again but checks his shot and just runs it down along the ground to long-on
Marsh crunches a cover-drive into the ground to the man in the ring
starts with a good ball, a touch of inswing and that's almost yorker length, Haddin is good enough though to drive a single down to long-off
Bresnan comes around the wicket to Marsh and gets the yorker length right again, Marsh can't get it away
tries the yorker again, just a touch short, and Marsh drives to cover
Marsh watches a late cut onto the bat from off middle stump
Bresnan bangs this in short, not called a wide but that must have been tight, was pretty high
more runs for Haddin, this could end very quickly if he can get much of the strike, he's latched on to a wide one and driven it in the air through cover for four more
another late cut from Marsh but this one can't beat short third man
good placement as Marsh drives through point to the man in the deep
Haddin again opens up and slogs this over cow corner! That's a slog, that's all there is to it, but a well struck one

very clever stuff from Haddin now as he uses his feet, deceives the bowler and gets back in his crease to steer this off the face between point and short third man, all the way along the ground for a boundary
driven down to mid-off and this one doesn't beat the field
Haddin backs off and crunches this down into the turf
touch too full as Bresnan tries for the yorker, Marsh clips it through midwicket
full and wide of off, Haddin's drive finds cover

Haddin continues to pepper cow corner, on one knee this time for what could almost be described as a slog sweep, he hasn't quite got enough of it to clear the boundary but it bounces just a couple of metres short
through midwicket along the ground now for a single, tame by Haddin's standards at the moment
angled in to the pads of Marsh, and that's what it hits
Marsh picks up one more with a drive in the air down towards long on
Marsh drives this away but can't beat point
Marsh gets a full one on the legs and flicks it away to short fine leg - can't beat the fielder though
this one does get fine enough though, Jordan strays on to the pads again and Marsh glances this away for four
Marsh drives down to long-off for a single
full again and Haddin drives a single to long-on, Australia are one clean hit away from a series win now
and there it is! Marsh clips over midwicket for a boundary and that is the match and the series! Australia have an unbeatable 3-0 lead
